comments: Zubac (LAC) reaches across Jokic's (DEN) body and makes contact after his gather, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Kennard (LAC) makes marginal contact with Barton (DEN) as he attempts to set the pick on the perimeter.
Zubac (LAC) moves laterally into Jokic's (DEN) path on the drive and affects his SQBR.
Jokic (DEN) extends his forearm into Jackson's (LAC) front and affects his SQBR.
Green (DEN) wraps Zubac (LAC) around the lower body as he is posting up, and the contact affects his ability to get to the incoming pass.
Barton (DEN) establishes himself in a screening position in Zubac's (LAC) path and absorbs the contact during the pick.
Kennard (LAC) makes marginal body contact with Jokic (DEN) on the perimeter, which he is able to move through.

Replay review of the foul called on Zubac (LAC) pursuant to a coach?s challenge was deemed successful. Zubac cleanly blocks Jokic's (DEN) shot attempt in the post prior to any incidental contact occurring.
Zubac (LAC) is jumping alongside Jokic's (DEN) path when marginal body contact occurs on the driving shot attempt.
Zubac (LAC) is firming up in a legal screening position in Gordon's (DEN) path and absorbs the contact during the pick.
Jokic (DEN) is moving alongside Jackson's (LAC) path with a resting forearm when marginal contact occurs on the driving shot attempt.
Coffey (LAC) jumps vertically and collapses his forearm when he contests Barton's (DEN) driving shot attempt.
LAC commits a 24-second chock clock violation.
Zubac (LAC) legally contests Jokic's (DEN) jump shot attempt and incidental contact occurs after Jokic's release as he naturally drifts toward Zubac.
Green (DEN) moves toward Boston Jr. (LAC) to contest the jump shot attempt and lower-body contact occurs after Boston Jr.'s release.
Jackson (LAC) jumps vertically and maintains a legal vertical position contesting the driving shot attempt by Green (DEN).
Jackson (LAC) legally contests Morris' (DEN) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Jackson (LAC) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact initiated by Morris (DEN) during the driving shot attempt.
Jokic (DEN) touches the ball while it is in the imaginary cylinder above the rim.
Green (DEN) is established in Jackson's (LAC) path prior to his upward motion and absorbs the body contact in the chest as Jackson dislodges him.
Jokic (DEN) extends his resting forearm slightly into Zubac (LAC) during the put-back shot attempt, and the contact is marginal.
Zubac (LAC) steps up and into Jokic's (DEN) body off-ball, affecting his FOM and impeding his ability to cut.

Coffey (LAC) makes clean contact with the ball during Jokic's (DEN) driving shot attempt. However, Jackson (LAC) reaches in and makes contact with Jokic's (DEN) arm. The foul should've been assessed to Jackson.
Boston Jr. (LAC) is attempting to firm up in Gordon's (DEN) path when marginal body contact occurs during the screen.
Green (DEN) jumps vertically and maintains a legal vertical position as he absorbs the body contact during Boston Jr.'s (LAC) driving shot attempt.
All Technical Fouls are reviewed by League Operations.
